{
  "sn": "Herald-Mage Revelation",
  "plot": "DEV: Rance reported Lisle's destruction to Circle; revealed Karsite involvement (Sun-Priests, blood magic, live captives for sacrifice); declared Mage-Gift manifestation—first in generations; established cover story (trainee quarters in remote healer's cottage); diplomatic inquiries ordered to neighboring nations. PEND: Talia's recovery timeline uncertain; Mage-Gift training with no living teachers; Karsite blood magic threat scope unknown; political implications of two people holding Queen's Own knowledge; Circle deliberating Rance's unprecedented status.",
  "entities": [
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Rance",
      "c": "IDENTITY: Former headman Lisle; newly Chosen by Senta; Herald-trainee (official cover). STATE: Physically stable post-Gift manifestation; possesses complete memory-merge with Talia (all state secrets, training, protocol, personal history). GIFT: Mage-Gift—first manifestation leveled Lisle; energy blast capability; untrained but demonstrating unprecedented control. COMMITMENT: Contingency with Senta to be knocked unconscious if loses control. PUBLIC POSITION: Assigned healer's cottage in Companion's Field for safety/discretion; officially 'trainee like any other' to buy time.",
      "k": ["Rance", "Herald-trainee"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Talia",
      "c": "STATE: Profoundly overwhelmed but recovering post-mind-merge; under Healer Crescent's care. MERGE AFTERMATH: Experienced Rance's Lisle memories directly; he worked through her buried trauma (arranged marriage escape, Empathy awakening, isolation, fear of losing identity, crushing responsibility as Queen's Own); first time allowing true vulnerability; walls between compartmentalized self dissolving. STANCE-Rance: Complete mutual knowledge from merge; he knows her deepest fears/secrets including wine preferences; intimacy of shared consciousness (kiss broke connection); conflicted emotions—violation yet gratitude, fear yet fascination; he promised to share burdens she carried alone. CAPABILITY: Full recovery expected; currently unable to perform Queen's Own duties.",
      "k": ["Talia", "Queen's Own"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Senta",
      "c": "STATE: Exhausted from hard travel; coat dulled with road dust and sweat; awaiting promised grooming. STANCE-Rance: Protective; impressed by his pragmatism and leadership; exasperated by his spite-driven impossible feats; proud of contingency planning. ROLE: Enforcing knockout contingency if needed; refusing separation during procedures; monitoring Gift responses; providing steady support through bond. OBSERVATIONS: Recognized Mage-Gift first; warned about Talia's Empathy reach; counseled diplomatic caution with Circle.",
      "k": ["Senta"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Queen Selenay",
      "c": "STANCE-Rance: Confirmed his mind-merge claim via wine preference detail (only Talia knew); acknowledges extraordinary burden carried; grateful for warning; calculating political ramifications of situation. CONCERNS: Security vulnerability of two people holding Queen's Own knowledge; Mage-Gift return after centuries; Talia's recovery timeline; no training protocols exist. ORDERS: Assigned Rance to healer's cottage; diplomatic inquiries to Karse's neighbors; information sealed to Circle only.",
      "k": ["Queen Selenay", "Selenay"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Rolan",
      "c": "STANCE-Rance: Positioned beside him throughout Circle meeting without his Chosen present; silent endorsement lending legitimacy; monitoring situation with grave concern tempered by hope; approval carries weight with Circle members.",
      "k": ["Rolan"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Healer Crescent",
      "c": "ASSESSMENT: Diagnosed Rance with Gift-shock of extraordinary magnitude, channels forced open, extensive mental pathway trauma; mind-merge should have killed both participants or driven them insane—physically stable outcome 'unfathomable'; cleared both for Circle meeting under observation mandate.",
      "k": ["Healer Crescent", "Crescent"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Weaponsmaster Alberich",
      "c": "STANCE-Rance: Tested via Vkandis greeting—passed by not taking offense (extremists would have); earned professional respect for caution. ASSESSMENT: Karsite evidence is special forces, officer-grade steel, recent manufacture (within 2 years), suggests state-sanctioned action not rogues. CONCERNS: Practical matters of Mage-Gift training/containment; security implications of two holding Queen's Own knowledge.",
      "k": ["Weaponsmaster Alberich", "Alberich", "Weaponsmaster"]
    },
    {
      "t": "lore",
      "n": "Mage-Gift Return",
      "c": "First manifestation in Valdemar since Vanyel's era; thought extinct for generations; no living teachers remain; archives may contain sealed Vanyel-era records. Rance's manifestation: energy blast leveling village; unprecedented untrained control (stabilized mind-merge, active shielding); coincides suspiciously with Karsite blood magic return. Title: Herald-Mage. Implications reshape Valdemar's power structure and magical capabilities.",
      "k": ["Mage-Gift", "Herald-Mage", "Vanyel"]
    },
    {
      "t": "lore",
      "n": "Karsite Blood Magic Threat",
      "c": "Sun-Priests conducting raids disguised as Menmellith bandits; taking live captives (including young/elderly) across borders for sacrifice/blood magic rituals; possibly demon summoning. Military-grade weapons (officer issue, special forces, <2yr old) indicate state sanction not rogue elements. Represents fundamental policy shift—blood sacrifice officially condemned for generations. Pattern: cyclical extremism returns during Karsite internal instability. Unknown if Valdemar uniquely targeted or broader campaign.",
      "k": ["Karsite Blood Magic", "Sun-Priests", "Karse"]
    },
    {
      "t": "location",
      "n": "Lisle",
      "c": "STATUS: Completely destroyed—crater remains where village stood; mostly ash, some partially intact attacker corpses; all residents killed or taken captive. LOCATION: Remote border village near Karse/Rethwellan/Menmellith crossroads; so isolated Crown assistance effectively nonexistent. ATTACK: Karsites disguised as Menmellith bandits; avoided killing blows to take prisoners alive for blood sacrifice.",
      "k": ["Lisle"]
    }
  ]
}
